File Handling:
    Reading/writing data to files through programing is called
    File Handling.

To Read/Write Data to file:
    1) We need location of the file
    2) We need to Navigate to the file
    3) We need a suitable class to read/write the data to a file

How to get the location of a file in IntelliJ?
    1) right-click on the file -> copy path reference -> Absolute path

How do we navigate to files through programing?
    We cause FileInputStream class to do the navigation.

Why do Testers use Configuration file?
    So that we can store sensitive information like username and
    passwords outside of the code

Why do Testers use Excel files?
    As a tester, we store testing data in Excel file. We store all of
    our data when we perform data-driven testing.
